To clarify, I list the three states of the iterator:
1. Uninitialized (`initialized == false && buffer.is_none()` in current code), before any `.next()` or `.advance_by()` called on the `MapWindows` iterator;
2. Initialized and active (`initialized == true && buffer.is_some()` in current code), since `.next()` or `.advance_by` called but not fused yet;
